If you are a Mexico resident, the following will apply:
Section 3 (Purposes for Processing) is amended as follows:
Purposes for Processing
The table below sets out:
our purpose for processing your personal data;
our legal justifications (each called a ‘legal basis’)
categories of personal data which we use for each purpose. See more about these categories in section 2 (Personal Data We Collect About You).
Here is a general explanation of each ‘legal basis’ to help you understand the table:
Performance of a Contract
: When it’s necessary for Abalta (or a third party) to process your personal data to:
comply with obligations under a contract with you, or
to verify information before a new contract with you begins.
Tacit Consent
. When you don’t object to the processing of your personal data, after having read the Privacy Policy.
Compliance with Legal Obligations
: When Abalta must process your personal data to comply with a law.
Primary purposes
Purposes for  processing your data
Legal basis for processing
Categories of personal data used for the purposes
To respond to your comments, requests, questions and inquiries that you submit by email or phone or through our Data Subject Request Form or our Website’s contact us form.
Tacit Consent
Identity or Contact Data
Communication Data
Usage Data
Device Data
To communicate with you about your comments, requests, questions and inquiries provided by email or phone or through Data Subject Request Form or our Website’s contact us form.
This may involve:
informing you of Abalta’s products, services, and promotional activities that may be of interest to you;
responding to your questions or inquiries, including customer service requests;
responding to your privacy inquiries; and
inviting you to participate in, or informing you of the results of, customer satisfaction or market research surveys.
Tacit Consent
Identity or Contact Data
Communication Data
Usage Data
Device Data
To provide WebLink® service.
Performance of a contract with you
Identity or Contact Data
Communication Data
Usage Data
Device Data
To establish, exercise, or defend legal claims.
For example, if we are involved in litigation and we need to provide information to our lawyers in relation to that legal case.
This include:
complying with our obligations to retain certain business records for minimum retention periods;
establishing, exercising, or defending legal claims;
complying with laws, regulations, court orders, or other legal processes;
detecting, preventing, and responding to fraud or intellectual property infringement claims, violations of our contracts or agreements, violations of law, or other misuse of our website, products or services; and
protecting the Abalta’s rights or property, or yours or others’ health, safety, welfare, rights, or property.
