Options to Limit the Use or Disclosure of Your Personal Data
In addition to what is established in section 11 (Your Rights and Choices) of the Privacy Policy, in order to allow you to limit the use and/or disclosure of your personal data, we offer you the following means:
Your registration with the Public Registry for Avoiding Advertising, which is under the responsibility of the Federal Consumer Protection Agency (Procuraduría Federal del Consumidor), with the purpose of preventing your personal data from being used to receive advertising or promotions from companies offering goods or services. For more information about this registry, you can visit the website of the Federal Consumer Protection Agency or contact them directly.
Cookies and Automatic Data Collection Technologies
In addition to what is established regarding cookies and automatic data collection technologies, which are subject to the described purposes, as well as the provisions related to data transfers and disclosure, you are informed that these technologies can be disabled by following the steps below:
Website (helloweblink.com):
You may choose to enable or disable cookies, except for strictly necessary cookies, from the cookie banner at the bottom of the homepage. Also, most web browsers allow some control of most cookies through the browser settings. You can configure your browser so that you are informed when cookies are set, or you can decide on an individual basis whether to accept cookies or reject the acceptance of cookies in general. Every browser differs in the management of cookie settings. They are available for the different browsers at the following links:
Microsoft Windows Explorer
Google Chrome
Mozilla Firefox
Apple Safari
For more information on the use of these technologies, please contact us through the channels indicated in the Contact Us section.
Changes to the Privacy Policy
We are committed to keeping you informed about any changes that may occur to this Privacy Policy. The procedure through which notifications about changes or updates will be made is as follows: we will notify you through an announcement on the homepage of our Website or on the WebLink Host App in the event that the changes are substantial.
